The paper deals with the problem of constructing orthogonal drawings of planar graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of flow-network algorithms and the NP-hardness result suggest that the paper also relates to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of optimization problems and the use of graph theory indicate a possible connection to game theory (cs.GT) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
